South African doctor: Although Omicron has strong transmission power, most of them are mild diseases
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the disease caused by the Omicron variant of covid-19 is more mild than that caused by the delta variant, although it spreads faster.
According to the associated press, with the spread of the Omicron variant in South Africa, a doctors' organization composed of more than 5000 doctors in Gauteng Province, South Africa, reported that the symptoms of the COVID-19 patients they currently treat are relatively mild, such as physical pain, cough and other flu-like symptoms.
Dr. Unben Pillay, director of the organization, said that he sees dozens of patients every day, but no patient needs to be hospitalized.
Pillay said, "they can control the disease at home, and most people recover within 10 to 14 days of isolation."
He said that this includes elderly patients and those with health problems, who would have been more vulnerable to severe coronavirus infection.
He said that in contrast, in the last wave of delta epidemic, the patients he treated with covid-19 had "dyspnea and low blood oxygen levels.
Many people will be hospitalized in a few days. "
Within two weeks after the first report of the Omicron variant in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
Although it will take a few weeks to collect enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the conclusion of the National Institute of infectious diseases in South Africa: in recent weeks, only 30% of the patients with covid-19 were serious diseases, half of the proportion of severe cases in the previous wave of the epidemic; The average length of stay was shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days; Only 3% of the recent covid-19 patients died, while 20% of the early outbreaks in South Africa.
Willem Hanekom, director of the African Institute of health, quoted data from the National Institute of infectious diseases and other reports as saying: "at present, almost all signs indicate that this is a mild disease."
He also said, "it is still early, and we need to obtain later data.
Usually, hospitalization and death occur later, and we only have two weeks to enter this epidemic. "
At the same time, scientists around the world are observing the number of cases and hospitalization rates, while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although delta is still the main covid-19 strain in the world, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa as the epidemic center.
According to health officials, the number of new cases found in Gauteng Province increased by 400% in the first week of December, and tests showed that more than 90% of cases were of the Omicron variant.
Education Review: What does it take to save abducted children?
If we draw an analogy with the famous public service advertisement saying "no sale, no killing," then in a good environment without the demand for "abduction," mass prevention and mass treatment, and anti abduction by the whole people will make abduction and trafficking unprofitable, risky, and costly, and such crimes will not occur frequently.
Recently, the emergency release platform for children's missing information developed by the Anti abduction Office of the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of public security went online.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of children's missing information and timely recover abducted children.
Hearing that this app is called "reunion," I suddenly feel warm.
New technological means are not only named "literature and art" and full of feelings, but also properly applied, practical and effective.
The primary goal of anti abduction law enforcement is to find the abducted child and protect his personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of suspects.
The significance of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can list many "big words."
However, before the abduction and trafficking case is solved, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victim.
There are priorities. Under the urgent purpose of "seeking help," controversial topics such as "whether abduction and trafficking of children should be subject to the death penalty" can be put on hold and discussed carefully; But the rescue of abducted children cannot wait.
According to the investigation experience of such cases, traffickers are used to leaving the crime site as soon as possible after they succeed.
If the abduction search is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step away from his parents, and the difficulty of case detection will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective method such as the "reunion" platform, which is directly conducive to the detection of cases and the recovery of children.
After all, "cracking down on abductions" is a major task that requires the operation of the entire legal system.
To combat crime and protect the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation to the protection of justice, as well as the meticulous law enforcement, we all need to implement the care of "protecting the young and supporting the weak."
In addition, the prevention of child abduction and trafficking, from the family to the society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three is resting at the railway station. Their parents are asleep and wake up to find that their children are missing.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, he should at least have a considerable sense of protection.
Parents take turns to rest, or put their children under safe protection, are the minimum means to prevent children from being abducted.
From the other side of the police's crackdown on the crime of abduction and trafficking, the party who buys abducted children should also be concerned and punished.
A single illegal act is often just a link in a long chain.
According to the criminal law of our country, the legal starting point of the crime of abducting and selling children is 5 years; If the circumstances are especially serious, he may be sentenced to death and concurrently be sentenced to confiscation of property.
The starting point is high and the maximum punishment is heavy. Under the general trend of "light punishment," the crime of abducting and selling children obviously belongs to the crime of heavier punishment.
But there are still many cases of abduction and trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people are backward in the concept of raising children and have weak legal awareness.
The legal education of these people should be followed up at the same time.
To effectively control the crime of abduction and trafficking, we cannot rely solely on the official strict law enforcement.
If the "market" for abduction is widespread, and the abductors are greedy for profits, constantly innovate the means of abduction and trafficking, and form a "law fight" situation with law enforcers, the anti abduction action is bound to fall into the mud of low efficiency.
Therefore, getting rid of backward ideas and popularizing legal common sense will also help eradicate the crime of abducting and selling children.
