Educational thinking: how to make "learning tyrants" and "learning dregs" take their place in college examinations - Xinhuanet
Three students of Lanzhou Jiaotong University wrote to the school leaders, reflecting their confusion about the university examination, and proposed to improve the difficulty of the examination, change the type of examination questions, and make the examination truly reflect the actual level of students.
Indeed, for a long time, college examinations have been a "hot topic."
On university campuses, students come from all over the world, and their ability levels are different. In addition, their learning levels are different.
It is inevitable that there are different feelings about the assessment of groups with such diverse characteristics.
Of course, if the examination questions are single, with high repetition rate, and the questions are too simple, it will inevitably cause another completely different feeling.
Students who don't work hard may pass the exam by concentrating on assault before the exam. If they think of other ways, they may achieve twice the result with half the effort.
In this way, there will be "learning dregs" who can pass the exam and even get high scores without investment at ordinary times; "Xueba" usually never misses classes, and his homework and notes are all good, and his exams are not much higher than the "strange status quo."
In this way, the students of Lanzhou Jiaotong University reflect that the problems existing in the university examination are not without reason, and I believe that this situation is not only in Lanzhou Jiaotong University.
In this sense, we should praise the three students who wrote directly.
In fact, people who have gone to college know that it is not uncommon to rush to prepare for the exam and find various ways to "get" the exam questions from the teacher, strive to draw the scope of the exam, and get "key guidance" before the exam. Even it is not strange to bring a cheat sheet in the exam and ask the teacher to raise his hand after the exam.
In the author's opinion, as a guidance of teaching quality evaluation, measuring whether a university exam is qualified or not depends more on teachers' comprehensive grasp of teaching and learning, as well as scientific propositions on this basis.
Entering the undergraduate stage, majors begin to be subdivided, and many professional courses are based on basic knowledge.
There is no doubt that whether to comprehensively master the basic knowledge of a subject is the content of the university examination.
However, undergraduate knowledge is basically subject basic theory and basic common sense. In terms of knowledge points, there is little room for change, and it is basically fixed.
As a teacher said, "20 years ago, I studied the basic knowledge of college mathematics, but now I'm still learning it, which is still the key."
However, the basic knowledge points remain unchanged, which does not mean that the examination questions are single and repeated.
In many universities, the examination will generally form a question group, and then the senior teachers of the subject will form the examination paper as a whole. The examination marking is also participated by all the teachers who undertake the subject, so that the repetition of the examination questions can be overcome to a certain extent.
However, to draw up a set of test questions that conform to the reality of teaching and learning, the difficulty and ease of the questions are normally distributed according to the overall situation of students' learning. It is also necessary to comprehensively grasp the teaching situation and comprehensively analyze the degree of students' learning, so that the test proposition has a dynamic grasp of the difficulty and ease and the question type, which can not only highlight the investigation of basic knowledge, but also take into account the ability examination, and carry out innovative design of the question type at the same time.
Examinations are the baton of university education. Students will have corresponding preparation plans for examinations. In the long run, it will affect the effectiveness of university education.
Lanzhou Jiaotong University attaches great importance to students' suggestions and has deployed a rectification plan throughout the school.
All teaching units are required to organize teachers to carry out discussions and self-examination of the course completion examination, formulate examination paper propositions and related systems, strengthen the supervision and inspection of examination paper propositions and audit links, refine the performance evaluation, and strengthen the comprehensive assessment of all links of course teaching.
To solve the problems of single type of examination questions and repeated questions from the mechanism is the issue that the university examination needs to face. Of course, corresponding systems need to be introduced, but kung fu is important in daily life. Teachers need to have a comprehensive grasp of the teaching situation, not only the teaching content, but also the students' learning situation. If they have a thorough understanding of both sides, teaching and learning will be better connected and form a benign interaction, and the examination will be more realistic, so that "learning tyrants" and "learning dregs" can get their own way.
