The Geminid meteor shower ushered in a great event on the 14th - Xinhuanet
Xinhua news agency, Tianjin, December 12 (reporter Zhou Runjian) - astronomical science experts said that as the last large-scale meteor shower of this year, the Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will usher in a great event on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the late night of that day.
The Geminid meteor shower was photographed by Beijing astronomer An Jiu in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
Most of the parent objects of the meteor shower are periodic comets, but the parent object of the Geminid meteor shower is asteroid faerton 3200, which is an Apollo asteroid.
The Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not "gestated" by comets.
Xiulipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert on astronomical science popularization, said that like the New Year blockbuster, the Geminid meteor shower generally appears at the end of the year, and the "release schedule" can last from December 4 to 17.
This meteor shower is famous for its large and stable flow. Together with the quadrant meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower, it is called the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere.
A remarkable feature of the Geminid meteor shower is that the meteoroids are slow, colorful, and there are many fire meteors. It is suitable for both visual and astronomical photography beginners.
The Geminid meteor shower was photographed by Tianjin astronomer Yang Jing in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
The astronomical forecast shows that this year's Geminid meteor shower will usher in a maximum at about 15:00 on December 14. The maximum ZHR (the number of meteors that can be seen per hour when the radiation point is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions) is 150.
Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart.
"Last year, the 'colorful' Geminid meteor shower left a deep impression on people, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the brilliance will be slightly discounted.
The 14th is November 11 of the lunar calendar, and the moon phase is a convex moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will set in the second half of the night, and the radiation point of the Geminid meteor shower will also rise relatively high at this time.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe them in the hours after midnight, but they should pay attention to keeping warm. "
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in the city. You can choose a place with high altitude, low light damage and an open field of vision facing the northeast in the suburbs or villages, and then wait patiently until the moon sets, and then observe visually.
It should be noted that the Geminid meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, so you don't have to keep staring at the radiation point of the Geminid meteor shower during observation.
If friends who like photography want to shoot gorgeous 'meteor shower blockbusters', they had better choose a wide-angle and large aperture lens, and use high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Based on stability and sustainability considerations, tripods, backup batteries and shutter wires are also essential. "
Xiulipeng reminded.
